<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="208" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,258,1948]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,258,283]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[414,617,259,283]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longilamellata">
<emphasis box="[414,617,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">H. longilamellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Phallus with membranous area covered with spicules and hook-like process apically (
<figureCitation box="[346,430,294,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
Fig. 
<number box="[398,430,295,319]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
); ejaculatory and gonocoxal apodemes very long (
<figureCitation box="[993,1166,294,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
Figs 39, 40, 
<number box="[1134,1166,295,319]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="208" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,258,1948]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,330,355]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[356,417,330,355]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[437,527,330,355]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
Fig. 
<number box="[495,527,330,355]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="36.0">36</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[551,615,330,355]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Head</emphasis>
. Dark brown to black, antenna and mouthparts yellow with all setae whitish. Strongly dorsoventrally flattened; ocellar triangle with 
<number box="[879,893,367,391]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of proclinate setae; anterior ocellus larger. Eyes iridescent black; close together on face bearing fine reclinate setulae. Frons with 
<number box="[1120,1134,403,427]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.0">1</number>
frontal setula; 
<number box="[1302,1344,403,427]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
pairs of vertical setae contiguous with uniseriate row of postocular setae. Occiput bearing scattered fine hairs. Clypeus with rather dense, short downwardly directed pile. Proboscis slightly curved with yellow setae. Antenna with scape and pedicel bearing distinct, short dorsal setulae; postpedicel about 
<number box="[888,922,511,535]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.3">1.3</number>
X as long as wide, stylus ~ 
<number box="[1253,1288,511,535]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="0.8">0.8</number>
X as long as postpedicel. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[296,385,546,571]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[403,491,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
Fig. 
<number box="[459,491,546,571]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="36.0">36</number>
</figureCitation>
). Elongate, slightly arched ventrally; thoracic dorsum yellow except brownish on prothoracic collar, narrowly behind postpronotal lobe, on scutum posterolaterally above wing base, and mediotergite; antepronotum with anterior margin almost straight and scutum with yellow setae, very small and fine except 
<number box="[232,246,655,679]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.0">1</number>
notopleural. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[398,454,654,679]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[471,556,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
Fig. 
<number box="[524,556,654,679]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="36.0">36</number>
</figureCitation>
). Whitish yellow. C 
<number box="[787,797,655,679]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[829,862,655,679]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.1">1.1</number>
X longer than distance between C 
<number box="[1254,1264,655,679]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.0">1</number>
and C2, 
<date box="[1370,1404,654,679]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">6X</date>
as long as wide with some pale dorsoapical setae. F 
<number box="[714,724,691,715]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.0">1</number>
about 
<number box="[804,838,691,715]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.2">1.2</number>
X as long as C 
<number box="[1013,1024,691,715]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.0">1</number>
, 4.0– 
<number box="[1088,1122,690,715]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="4.5">4.5</number>
X as long as wide. Femoral formula 
<number box="[249,262,726,751]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="7.0">7</number>
/ 
<number box="[271,344,726,751]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="23.5" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="23.0">23–24</number>
/ 
<number box="[354,363,726,751]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[378,450,726,751]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="20.5" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="20.0">20–21</number>
/ 
<number box="[459,501,726,751]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7</number>
; denticles confined to distal 
<number box="[834,871,727,751]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="0.8">0.8</number>
, becoming closer together distally, black, 
<number box="[1358,1372,727,751]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="2.0">2</number>
rows linear, without distal discontinuity, converging apically and diverging at extreme apex. T 
<number box="[1169,1179,763,787]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[1212,1247,763,787]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="0.7">0.7</number>
X as long as F 
<number box="[1420,1431,763,787]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.0">1</number>
, evenly curved, ventral face shallowly concave; about 
<number box="[748,818,799,823]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="20.0" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="19.0">19–21</number>
sharply pointed spinose setae ventrally; dorsal ciliation of decumbent short pale setulae, denser distally; without apicoventral extension on T 
<number box="[1116,1127,835,859]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.0">1</number>
, with short black subapical spine. Mid- and hind legs slender with fine setae; T 
<number box="[742,754,871,895]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="3.0">3</number>
with ‘comb’ of short setae posteroapically. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1256,1321,870,895]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1338,1423,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1423,871,895]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="37.0">37</number>
</figureCitation>
). Membrane slightly yellow, veins brownish; R 
<number box="[667,675,921,935]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[684,691,921,935]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="3.0">3</number>
long and straight, not strongly curved towards C apically, joining C ~ 
<number box="[200,235,946,970]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="0.7">0.7</number>
distance between end of R 
<number box="[541,549,960,974]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.0">1</number>
and R 
<number box="[624,632,960,974]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[641,648,960,974]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="5.0">5</number>
; R 
<number box="[682,690,960,974]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[699,706,960,974]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="5.0">5</number>
fork angle acute (~ 
<number box="[936,969,945,970]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="60.0">60</number>
°); distal to position of M 
<number box="[1252,1257,960,974]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[1267,1276,960,974]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="2.0">2</number>
fork by about 2.0X as long as R 
<number box="[350,358,999,1013]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="4.0">4</number>
; R 
<number box="[391,399,999,1013]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[478,486,999,1013]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.0">1</number>
almost parallel; R 
<number box="[693,701,999,1013]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="5.0">5</number>
~ 
<date box="[730,764,984,1008]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
<number box="[730,743,984,1008]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
as long as R 
<number box="[908,916,999,1013]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="4.0">4</number>
; cell bm+dm short, ending at level of R 
<number box="[1364,1372,999,1013]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="1.0">1</number>
, ~ 
<date box="[1401,1436,984,1008]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
<number box="[1401,1415,984,1008]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
as long as cell br. Halter whitish yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[615,731,1022,1047]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[748,834,1022,1047]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
Fig. 
<number box="[802,834,1022,1047]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="36.0">36</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tergites 
<number box="[952,994,1022,1047]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="3.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="1.0">1–6</number>
and 
<number box="[1051,1065,1023,1047]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="8.0">8</number>
brownish; tergite 
<number box="[1272,1286,1024,1047]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="7.0">7</number>
and sternites yellowish. Tergite 
<number box="[368,382,1059,1083]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="8.0">8</number>
longer than sternite 
<number box="[631,647,1059,1083]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="8.0">8</number>
; membranous area between segment 
<number box="[1088,1102,1059,1083]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="8.0">8</number>
and terminalia. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1298,1429,1059,1084]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Cercus brown, narrow, pointed apically (
<figureCitation box="[615,747,1094,1119]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Figs 38, 39</figureCitation>
), left and right cerci separated anterodorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1280,1365,1094,1119]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
Fig. 
<number box="[1333,1365,1095,1119]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="40.0">40</number>
</figureCitation>
), with distinct setae on outer face. Epandrium wide, subrectangular with rounded apex (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1156,1131,1156]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
Fig. 
<number box="[1125,1156,1131,1155]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
); with scattered setae on outer face. Surstylus subrounded, with distinct setae apically (
<figureCitation box="[862,947,1166,1191]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
Fig. 
<number box="[916,947,1167,1191]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
); articulated to hypandrium by weak point anteriorly. Hypandrium yellow, rather subtriangular, not markedly inflated, with distinct setae (
<figureCitation box="[1280,1423,1203,1228]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Figs 41, 43</figureCitation>
); gonocoxal apodeme very long, projecting much beyond anterior margin of hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[1139,1269,1238,1263]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Figs 39, 40</figureCitation>
). Subepandrial sclerite with quadrate anterior margin, with median rounded process posteriorly. Phallus sclerotized basally, with pointed dorsal projection apically and membranous area covered with spicules and hook-like process apically (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,183,1347,1371]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme unilamellar, flattened plate laterally, ~ 
<number box="[872,907,1347,1372]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="0.5">0.5</number>
X as long as gonocoxal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[1293,1424,1347,1372]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Figs 39, 40</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,347,1383,1408]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Specimen length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[362,451,1383,1407]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[463,601,1383,1408]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">wing length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[617,706,1383,1407]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[716,803,1383,1408]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
