<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="208" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,258,1948]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1707,1732]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[323,645,1707,1731]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="membranosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[323,645,1707,1731]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Hemerodromia membranosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[653,744,1707,1732]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[653,744,1707,1732]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
appears to belong to the same group of species that includes 
<taxonomicName box="[151,292,1743,1767]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamellata">
<emphasis box="[151,292,1743,1767]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">H. lamellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[307,506,1743,1767]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longilamellata">
<emphasis box="[307,506,1743,1767]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">H. longilamellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[563,764,1743,1767]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megalamellata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[563,764,1743,1767]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">H. megalamellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[772,863,1743,1768]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[772,863,1743,1768]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, which share very long ejaculatory and gonocoxal apodemes. 
<taxonomicName box="[282,608,1779,1803]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="membranosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[282,608,1779,1803]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Hemerodromia membranosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[619,714,1779,1804]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[619,714,1779,1804]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[880,1083,1779,1803]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longilamellata">
<emphasis box="[880,1083,1779,1803]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">H. longilamellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the cercus pointed apically (
<figureCitation box="[255,338,1815,1840]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
Fig. 
<number box="[309,338,1815,1839]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
) and epandrium rounded apically (
<figureCitation box="[734,819,1815,1840]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
Fig. 
<number box="[787,819,1815,1839]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[839,1160,1815,1839]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="membranosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[839,1160,1815,1839]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">Hemerodromia membranosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1168,1258,1815,1840]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1168,1258,1815,1840]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megalamellata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">H. megalamellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[327,419,1851,1876]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[327,419,1851,1876]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
by phallus with membranous area covered with spicules and hook-like process apically (
<figureCitation box="[159,246,1887,1912]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,195,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[181,1405,195,1871]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Hemerodromia membranosa sp. nov., 36 – 37, holotype ♂. 38 – 43, paratype ♂. 36, habitus, lateral view; 37, wing; 38, abdomen from tergite 5 to terminalia, lateral view; 39, terminalia, lateral view; 40, terminalia, dorsal view; 41, terminalia, ventral view; 42, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 43, hypandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233678/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,246,1887,1911]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
). The phallus of 
<taxonomicName box="[444,644,1887,1911]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longilamellata">
<emphasis box="[444,644,1887,1911]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">H. longilamellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a narrow membranous area apically and lacks scattered spicules (
<bibRefCitation author="Camara" box="[158,383,1923,1947]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" refString="Camara, J. T., Plant, A. R. &amp; Rafael, J. A. (2014) Neotropical Hemerodromia Meigen (Diptera: Empididae), a world of discovery I: New generic record and new species from Brazilian Amazon basin. Zootaxa, 3893 (2), 209 - 231. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3893.2.3" type="journal article" year="2014">
Câmara 
<emphasis box="[254,303,1923,1947]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="208">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number box="[324,383,1923,1947]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 
<number box="[439,471,1923,1948]" pageId="11" pageNumber="208" value="60.0">60</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
